HEADWORD: Encomium
<hw>En*co"mi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Encomiums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ (a song)
chanted in a Bacchic festival in praise of the god; <?/ in + <?/ a
jovial festivity, revel. See <er>Comedy</er>.]</ety> <def>Warm or high
praise; panegyric; strong commendation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>encomiums</qex> awakened all my ardor.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Irving.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Eulogy</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

